{
  "video_id": "sLiM2-izFl4",
  "title": "Lemn Sissay: A child of the state",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Joseph Geni Reviewer: Morton Bast"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16123.000000000002,
      "end_time": 20369.0,
      "text": "Having spent 18 years as a child of the state"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 20369.0,
      "end_time": 22675.0,
      "text": "in children&#39;s homes and foster care,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22675.0,
      "end_time": 25723.0,
      "text": "you could say that I&#39;m an expert on the subject,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 25723.0,
      "end_time": 29281.0,
      "text": "and in being an expert, I want to let you know that"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 29281.0,
      "end_time": 34888.0,
      "text": "being an expert does in no way make you right"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 34888.0,
      "end_time": 37888.0,
      "text": "in light of the truth."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 37888.0,
      "end_time": 42760.0,
      "text": "If you&#39;re in care, legally the government is your"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 42760.0,
      "end_time": 45803.0,
      "text": "parent, loco parentis."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 45803.0,
      "end_time": 49751.0,
      "text": "Margaret Thatcher was my mother. (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 49752.0,
      "end_time": 53401.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s not talk about breastfeeding. (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 53401.0,
      "end_time": 56539.0,
      "text": "Harry Potter was a foster child."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 56539.0,
      "end_time": 61579.0,
      "text": "Pip from \"Great Expectations\" was adopted;"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 61579.0,
      "end_time": 64661.0,
      "text": "Superman was a foster child;"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 64661.0,
      "end_time": 68189.0,
      "text": "Cinderella was a foster child;"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 68189.0,
      "end_time": 71797.0,
      "text": "Lisbeth Salander, the girl with the dragon tattoo,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 71797.0,
      "end_time": 74719.0,
      "text": "was fostered and institutionalized;"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 74719.0,
      "end_time": 79940.0,
      "text": "Batman was orphaned;"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 79940.0,
      "end_time": 82791.0,
      "text": "Lyra Belacqua from Philip Pullman&#39;s \"Northern Lights\""
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 82792.0,
      "end_time": 84481.0,
      "text": "was fostered;"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 84481.0,
      "end_time": 87216.0,
      "text": "Jane Eyre, adopted;"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 87216.0,
      "end_time": 91798.0,
      "text": "Roald Dahl&#39;s James from \"James and the Giant Peach;\""
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 91799.0,
      "end_time": 97311.0,
      "text": "Matilda; Moses -- Moses! (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 97311.0,
      "end_time": 99758.0,
      "text": "Moses! (Laughter) --"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 99758.0,
      "end_time": 104253.0,
      "text": "the boys in Michael Morpurgo&#39;s \"Friend or Foe;\""
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 104254.0,
      "end_time": 108700.0,
      "text": "Alem in Benjamin Zephaniah&#39;s \"Refugee Boy;\""
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 108700.0,
      "end_time": 110654.0,
      "text": "Luke Skywalker --"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 110654.0,
      "end_time": 113524.0,
      "text": "Luke Skywalker! (Laughter) --"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 113525.0,
      "end_time": 115812.0,
      "text": "Oliver Twist;"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 115812.0,
      "end_time": 120230.0,
      "text": "Cassia in \"The Concubine of Shanghai\" by Hong Ying;"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 120230.0,
      "end_time": 123380.0,
      "text": "Celie in Alice Walker&#39;s \"The Color Purple.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 123380.0,
      "end_time": 127991.0,
      "text": "All of these great fictional characters, all of them"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 127992.0,
      "end_time": 131989.0,
      "text": "who were hurt by their condition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 131989.0,
      "end_time": 136637.0,
      "text": "all of them who spawned thousands of other books"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 136637.0,
      "end_time": 139920.0,
      "text": "and other films, all of them"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 139920.0,
      "end_time": 143245.0,
      "text": "were fostered, adopted or orphaned."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 143245.0,
      "end_time": 148809.0,
      "text": "It seems that writers know that the child"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 148809.0,
      "end_time": 155958.0,
      "text": "outside of family reflects on what family truly is"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 155958.0,
      "end_time": 159548.0,
      "text": "more than what it promotes itself to be."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 159548.0,
      "end_time": 164515.0,
      "text": "That is, they also use extraordinary skills"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 164515.0,
      "end_time": 169344.0,
      "text": "to deal with extraordinary situations on a daily basis."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 169344.0,
      "end_time": 172866.0,
      "text": "How have we not made the connection?"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 172866.0,
      "end_time": 176904.0,
      "text": "And why have we not made the connection, between"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 176904.0,
      "end_time": 179103.0,
      "text": "— How has that happened? —"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 179104.0,
      "end_time": 182672.0,
      "text": "between these incredible characters of popular culture"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 182672.0,
      "end_time": 187760.0,
      "text": "and religions, and the fostered, adopted or orphaned child"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 187760.0,
      "end_time": 192392.0,
      "text": "in our midst? It&#39;s not our pity that they need."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 192392.0,
      "end_time": 194993.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s our respect."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 194993.0,
      "end_time": 197609.0,
      "text": "I know famous musicians,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 197610.0,
      "end_time": 202682.0,
      "text": "I know actors and film stars and millionaires and novelists"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 202682.0,
      "end_time": 206183.0,
      "text": "and top lawyers and television executives"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 206183.0,
      "end_time": 208632.0,
      "text": "and magazine editors and national journalists"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 208633.0,
      "end_time": 211474.0,
      "text": "and dustbinmen and hairdressers, all who were"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 211474.0,
      "end_time": 215100.0,
      "text": "looked after children, fostered, adopted or orphaned,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 215100.0,
      "end_time": 217682.0,
      "text": "and many of them grow into their adult lives"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 217682.0,
      "end_time": 221952.0,
      "text": "in fear of speaking of their background, as if it may"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 221953.0,
      "end_time": 226260.0,
      "text": "somehow weaken their standing in the foreground,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 226260.0,
      "end_time": 230302.0,
      "text": "as if it were somehow Kryptonite, as if it were a time bomb"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 230302.0,
      "end_time": 234349.0,
      "text": "strapped on the inside. Children in care,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 234349.0,
      "end_time": 237482.0,
      "text": "who&#39;ve had a life in care, deserve the right"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 237483.0,
      "end_time": 243333.0,
      "text": "to own and live the memory of their own childhood."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 243333.0,
      "end_time": 245612.0,
      "text": "It is that simple."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 245612.0,
      "end_time": 249618.0,
      "text": "My own mother — and I should say this here —"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 249618.0,
      "end_time": 253472.0,
      "text": "she same to this country in the late &#39;60s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 253472.0,
      "end_time": 257237.0,
      "text": "and she was, you know, she found herself pregnant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 257237.00000000003,
      "end_time": 259332.00000000003,
      "text": "as women did in the late &#39;60s. You know what I mean?"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 259332.0,
      "end_time": 261281.0,
      "text": "They found themselves pregnant."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 261281.0,
      "end_time": 265955.0,
      "text": "And she sort of, she had no idea of the context"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 265955.0,
      "end_time": 270750.0,
      "text": "in which she&#39;d landed."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 270750.0,
      "end_time": 273923.0,
      "text": "In the 1960s -- I should give you some context -- in the 1960s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 273923.0,
      "end_time": 277274.0,
      "text": "if you were pregnant and you were single,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 277274.0,
      "end_time": 280175.0,
      "text": "you were seen as a threat to the community."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 280175.0,
      "end_time": 286340.0,
      "text": "You were separated from your family by the state."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 286340.0,
      "end_time": 288736.0,
      "text": "You were separated from your family and placed into"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 288736.0,
      "end_time": 290858.0,
      "text": "mother and baby homes."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 290858.0,
      "end_time": 293999.0,
      "text": "You were appointed a social worker."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 293999.0,
      "end_time": 296389.0,
      "text": "The adoptive parents were lined up."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 296389.0,
      "end_time": 300474.0,
      "text": "It was the primary purpose of the social worker, the aim,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 300474.0,
      "end_time": 303815.0,
      "text": "to get the woman at her most vulnerable time"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 303815.0,
      "end_time": 309168.0,
      "text": "in her entire life, to sign the adoption papers."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 309168.0,
      "end_time": 311530.0,
      "text": "So the adoption papers were signed."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 311530.0,
      "end_time": 314623.0,
      "text": "The mother and baby&#39;s homes were often run by nuns."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 314623.0,
      "end_time": 317799.0,
      "text": "The adoption papers were signed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 317799.0,
      "end_time": 321495.0,
      "text": "the child was given to the adoptive parents, and the mother"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 321495.0,
      "end_time": 323919.0,
      "text": "shipped back to her community"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 323919.0,
      "end_time": 326909.0,
      "text": "to say that she&#39;d been on a little break."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 326910.0,
      "end_time": 329596.0,
      "text": "A little break."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 329596.0,
      "end_time": 331274.0,
      "text": "A little break."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 331274.0,
      "end_time": 334839.0,
      "text": "The first secret of shame for a woman"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 334839.0,
      "end_time": 339918.0,
      "text": "for being a woman, \"a little break.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 339918.0,
      "end_time": 343900.0,
      "text": "The adoption process took, like, a matter of months,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 343900.0,
      "end_time": 346889.0,
      "text": "so it was a closed shop, you know, sealed deal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 346889.0,
      "end_time": 353394.0,
      "text": "an industrious, utilitarian solution:"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 353394.0,
      "end_time": 356752.0,
      "text": "the government, the farmer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 356752.0,
      "end_time": 360599.0,
      "text": "the adopting parents, the consumer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 360599.0,
      "end_time": 365401.0,
      "text": "the mother, the earth, and the child, the crop."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 365401.0,
      "end_time": 370550.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s kind of easy to patronize the past,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 370550.0,
      "end_time": 374959.0,
      "text": "to forego our responsibilities in the present."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 374959.0,
      "end_time": 378811.0,
      "text": "What happened then is a direct reflection"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 378811.0,
      "end_time": 384540.0,
      "text": "of what is happening now. Everybody believed themselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 384550.0,
      "end_time": 388592.0,
      "text": "to be doing the right thing by God and by the state"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 388592.0,
      "end_time": 395479.0,
      "text": "for the big society, fast-tracking adoption."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 395479.0,
      "end_time": 400671.0,
      "text": "So anyway, she comes here, 1967, she&#39;s pregnant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 400672.0,
      "end_time": 405750.0,
      "text": "and she comes from Ethiopia that was celebrating"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 405750.0,
      "end_time": 408448.0,
      "text": "its own jubilee at the time"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 408448.0,
      "end_time": 411217.0,
      "text": "under the Emperor Haile Selassie,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 411218.0,
      "end_time": 416344.0,
      "text": "and she lands months before the Enoch Powell speech,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 416344.0,
      "end_time": 418464.0,
      "text": "the \"Rivers of Blood\" speech."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 418464.0,
      "end_time": 423860.0,
      "text": "She lands months before the Beatles release \"The White Album,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 423860.0,
      "end_time": 425770.0,
      "text": "months before Martin Luther King was killed."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 425770.0,
      "end_time": 428221.0,
      "text": "It was a summer of love if you were white."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 428221.0,
      "end_time": 431913.0,
      "text": "If you were black, it was a summer of hate."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 431913.0,
      "end_time": 437563.0,
      "text": "So she goes from Oxford, she&#39;s sent to the north of England"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 437563.0,
      "end_time": 441923.0,
      "text": "to a mother and baby home, and appointed a social worker."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 441923.0,
      "end_time": 446163.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s her plan. You know, I have to say this in the Houses --"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 446163.0,
      "end_time": 450434.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s her plan to have me fostered for a short period of time"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 450434.0,
      "end_time": 454900.0,
      "text": "while she studies. But the social worker,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 454900.0,
      "end_time": 457300.0,
      "text": "he had a different agenda."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 457300.0,
      "end_time": 461210.0,
      "text": "He found the foster parents, and he said to them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 461210.0,
      "end_time": 465420.0,
      "text": "\"Treat this as an adoption. He&#39;s yours forever."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 465420.0,
      "end_time": 468489.0,
      "text": "His name is Norman.\" (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 468489.0,
      "end_time": 470825.0,
      "text": "Norman! (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 470826.0,
      "end_time": 473538.0,
      "text": "Norman!"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 473538.0,
      "end_time": 479764.0,
      "text": "So they took me. I was a message, they said."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 479764.0,
      "end_time": 482223.0,
      "text": "I was a sign from God, they said."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 482223.0,
      "end_time": 485967.0,
      "text": "I was Norman Mark Greenwood."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 485967.0,
      "end_time": 489385.0,
      "text": "Now, for the next 11 years, all I know is that this woman,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 489386.0,
      "end_time": 491974.0,
      "text": "this birth woman, should have her eyes scratched out"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 491974.0,
      "end_time": 494976.0,
      "text": "for not signing the adoption papers. She was an evil woman"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 494976.0,
      "end_time": 498530.0,
      "text": "too selfish to sign, so I spent those 11 years"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 498530.0,
      "end_time": 500808.0,
      "text": "kneeling and praying."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 500809.0,
      "end_time": 503930.0,
      "text": "I tried praying. I swear I tried praying."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 503930.0,
      "end_time": 507738.0,
      "text": "\"God, can I have a bike for Christmas?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 507738.0,
      "end_time": 512860.0,
      "text": "But I would always answer myself, \"Yes, of course you can.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 512860.0,
      "end_time": 513700.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 513700.00000000006,
      "end_time": 516437.00000000006,
      "text": "And then I was supposed to determine whether that"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 516437.0,
      "end_time": 519969.0,
      "text": "was the voice of God or it was the voice of the Devil."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 519969.00000000006,
      "end_time": 527328.0,
      "text": "And it turns out I&#39;ve got the Devil inside of me."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 527328.0,
      "end_time": 529736.0,
      "text": "Who knew? (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 529736.0,
      "end_time": 532632.0,
      "text": "So anyway, two years sort of passed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 532632.0,
      "end_time": 534410.0,
      "text": "and they had a child of their own,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 534410.0,
      "end_time": 536874.0,
      "text": "and then another two years passed, and they had another child of their own,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 536874.0,
      "end_time": 539165.0,
      "text": "and then another time passed"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 539165.0,
      "end_time": 541742.0,
      "text": "and they had another child that they called an accident,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 541742.0,
      "end_time": 545150.0,
      "text": "which I thought was an unusual name. (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 545150.0,
      "end_time": 548879.0,
      "text": "And I was on the cusp of, sort of, adolescence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 548879.0,
      "end_time": 553284.0,
      "text": "so I was starting to take biscuits from the tin without asking."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 553284.0,
      "end_time": 557610.0,
      "text": "I was starting to stay out a little bit late, etc., etc."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 557610.0,
      "end_time": 560464.0,
      "text": "Now, in their religiosity, in their naivete,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 560464.0,
      "end_time": 562901.0,
      "text": "my mom and dad, which I believed them to be forever,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 562901.0,
      "end_time": 566169.0,
      "text": "as they said they were, my mom and dad"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 566169.0,
      "end_time": 572978.0,
      "text": "conceived that I had the Devil inside of me."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 572978.0,
      "end_time": 575360.0,
      "text": "And what -- I should say this here, because this is how"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 575360.0,
      "end_time": 576994.0,
      "text": "they engineered my leaving."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 576995.0,
      "end_time": 580384.0,
      "text": "They sat me at a table, my foster mom, and she said to me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 580384.0,
      "end_time": 582452.0,
      "text": "\"You don&#39;t love us, do you?\" At 11 years old."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 582452.0,
      "end_time": 585961.0,
      "text": "They&#39;ve had three other children. I&#39;m the fourth. The third was an accident."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 585961.0,
      "end_time": 590600.0,
      "text": "And I said, \"Yeah, of course I do.\" Because you do."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 590600.0,
      "end_time": 592156.0,
      "text": "My foster mother asked me to go away to think about love"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 592157.0,
      "end_time": 595100.0,
      "text": "and what it is and to read the Scriptures and to come back tomorrow"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 595100.0,
      "end_time": 597944.0,
      "text": "and give my most honest and truthful answer."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 597944.0,
      "end_time": 600784.0,
      "text": "So this was an opportunity. If they were asking me"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 600784.0,
      "end_time": 603120.0,
      "text": "whether I loved them or not, then I mustn&#39;t love them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 603120.0,
      "end_time": 605985.0,
      "text": "which led me to the miracle of thought that I thought they wanted me to get to."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 605985.0,
      "end_time": 608656.0,
      "text": "\"I will ask God for forgiveness and His light will shine"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 608656.0,
      "end_time": 612424.0,
      "text": "through me to them. How fantastic.\" This was an opportunity."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 612424.0,
      "end_time": 615209.0,
      "text": "The theology was perfect, the timing unquestionable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 615209.0,
      "end_time": 618112.0,
      "text": "and the answer as honest as a sinner could get."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 618112.0,
      "end_time": 622800.0,
      "text": "\"I mustn&#39;t love you,\" I said to them. \"But I will ask God for forgiveness.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 622800.0,
      "end_time": 625352.0,
      "text": "\"Because you don&#39;t love us, Norman,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 625352.0,
      "end_time": 627696.0,
      "text": "clearly you&#39;ve chosen your path.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 627696.0,
      "end_time": 630494.0,
      "text": "Twenty-four hours later, my social worker,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 630494.0,
      "end_time": 633543.0,
      "text": "this strange man who used to visit me every couple of months,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 633543.0,
      "end_time": 636755.0,
      "text": "he&#39;s waiting for me in the car as I say goodbye to my parents."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 636755.0,
      "end_time": 639331.0,
      "text": "I didn&#39;t say goodbye to anybody, not my mother, my father,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 639331.0,
      "end_time": 641159.0,
      "text": "my sisters, my brothers, my aunts, my uncles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 641159.0,
      "end_time": 644788.0,
      "text": "my cousins, my grandparents, nobody."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 644788.0,
      "end_time": 648335.0,
      "text": "On the way to the children&#39;s home, I started to ask myself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 648335.0,
      "end_time": 651310.0,
      "text": "\"What&#39;s happened to me?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 651310.0,
      "end_time": 654463.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not that I&#39;d had the rug pulled from beneath me"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 654463.0,
      "end_time": 659278.0,
      "text": "as much as the entire floor had been taken away."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 659278.0,
      "end_time": 663780.0,
      "text": "When I got to the —"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 663780.0,
      "end_time": 667461.0,
      "text": "For the next four, five years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 667461.0,
      "end_time": 672314.0,
      "text": "I was held in four different children&#39;s homes."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 672314.0,
      "end_time": 675591.0,
      "text": "On the third children&#39;s home, at 15,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 675591.0,
      "end_time": 678758.0,
      "text": "I started to rebel, and what I did was,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 678758.0,
      "end_time": 683870.0,
      "text": "I got three tins of paint, Airfix paint that you use for models,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 683870.0,
      "end_time": 686918.0,
      "text": "and I was -- it was a big children&#39;s home, big Victorian children&#39;s home --"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 686918.0,
      "end_time": 688758.0,
      "text": "and I was in a little turret at the top of it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 688758.0,
      "end_time": 692610.0,
      "text": "and I poured them, red, yellow and green,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 692610.0,
      "end_time": 697102.0,
      "text": "the colors of Africa, down the tiles."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 697102.0,
      "end_time": 699606.0,
      "text": "You couldn&#39;t see it from the street, because the home"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 699606.0,
      "end_time": 702580.0,
      "text": "was surrounded by beech trees."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 702580.0,
      "end_time": 707140.0,
      "text": "For doing this, I was incarcerated for a year"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 707140.0,
      "end_time": 709999.0,
      "text": "in an assessment center which was actually"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 709999.0,
      "end_time": 714719.0,
      "text": "a remand center. It was a virtual prison"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 714719.0,
      "end_time": 718617.0,
      "text": "for young people."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 718617.0,
      "end_time": 720670.0,
      "text": "By the way, years later, my social worker said"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 720670.0,
      "end_time": 722128.0,
      "text": "that I should never have been put in there."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 722129.0,
      "end_time": 724784.0,
      "text": "I wasn&#39;t charged for anything. I hadn&#39;t done anything wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 724784.0,
      "end_time": 729510.0,
      "text": "But because I had no family to inquire about me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 729510.0,
      "end_time": 734261.0,
      "text": "they could do anything to me."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 734261.0,
      "end_time": 737615.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m 17 years old, and"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 737615.0,
      "end_time": 741256.0,
      "text": "they had a padded cell."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 741256.0,
      "end_time": 747216.0,
      "text": "They would march me down corridors in last-size order."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 747216.0,
      "end_time": 749481.0,
      "text": "They -- I was put in a dormitory"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 749481.0,
      "end_time": 753401.0,
      "text": "with a confirmed Nazi sympathizer."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 753401.0,
      "end_time": 756723.0,
      "text": "All of the staff were ex-police -- interesting --"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 756723.0,
      "end_time": 758737.0,
      "text": "and ex-probation officers."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 758737.0,
      "end_time": 762800.0,
      "text": "The man who ran it was an ex-army officer."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 762800.0,
      "end_time": 765959.0,
      "text": "Every time I had a visit by a person who I did not know"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 765960.0,
      "end_time": 769694.0,
      "text": "who would feed me grapes, once every three months,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 769694.0,
      "end_time": 771905.0,
      "text": "I was strip-searched."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 771905.0,
      "end_time": 775158.0,
      "text": "That home was full of young boys who were on remand"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 775158.0,
      "end_time": 780426.0,
      "text": "for things like murder."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 780426.0,
      "end_time": 784458.0,
      "text": "And this was the preparation that I was being given"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 784458.0,
      "end_time": 790509.0,
      "text": "after 17 years as a child of the state."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 790509.0,
      "end_time": 793920.0,
      "text": "I have to tell this story."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 793920.0,
      "end_time": 795362.0,
      "text": "I have to tell it, because there was no one"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 795362.0,
      "end_time": 798314.0,
      "text": "to put two and two together."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 798315.0,
      "end_time": 801342.0,
      "text": "I slowly became aware that I knew nobody"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 801342.0,
      "end_time": 804836.0,
      "text": "that knew me for longer than a year."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 804836.0,
      "end_time": 807685.0,
      "text": "See, that&#39;s what family does."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 807685.0,
      "end_time": 810750.0,
      "text": "It gives you reference points."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 810760.0,
      "end_time": 812564.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m not defining a good family from a bad family."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 812564.0,
      "end_time": 814380.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m just saying that you know when your birthday is"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 814380.0,
      "end_time": 817360.0,
      "text": "by virtue of the fact that somebody tells you when your birthday is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 817360.0,
      "end_time": 818983.0,
      "text": "a mother, a father, a sister, a brother, an aunt, an uncle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 818983.0,
      "end_time": 820992.0,
      "text": "a cousin, a grandparent. It matters to someone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 820993.0,
      "end_time": 823280.0,
      "text": "and therefore it matters to you. Understand,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 823280.0,
      "end_time": 827509.0,
      "text": "I was 14 years old, tucked away in myself, into myself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 827509.0,
      "end_time": 832291.0,
      "text": "and I wasn&#39;t touched either, physically touched."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 832291.0,
      "end_time": 840418.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m reporting back. I&#39;m reporting back simply to say that"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 840418.0,
      "end_time": 843633.0,
      "text": "when I left the children&#39;s home I had two things"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 843633.0,
      "end_time": 847430.0,
      "text": "that I wanted to do. One was to find my family,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 847430.0,
      "end_time": 848959.0,
      "text": "and the other was to write poetry."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 848960.0,
      "end_time": 851509.0,
      "text": "In creativity I saw light."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 851509.0,
      "end_time": 856671.0,
      "text": "In the imagination I saw the endless possibility of life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 856671.0,
      "end_time": 862572.0,
      "text": "the endless truth, the permanent creation of reality,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 862572.0,
      "end_time": 869350.0,
      "text": "the place where anger was an expression"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 869350.0,
      "end_time": 872783.0,
      "text": "in the search for love, a place where dysfunction"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 872783.0,
      "end_time": 877501.0,
      "text": "is a true reaction to untruth."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 877501.0,
      "end_time": 881480.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve just got to say it to you all: I found all of my family"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 881480.0,
      "end_time": 884411.0,
      "text": "in my adult life. I spent all of my adult life finding them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 884411.0,
      "end_time": 888425.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;ve now got a fully dysfunctional family just like everybody else."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 888426.0,
      "end_time": 892166.0,
      "text": "But I&#39;m reporting back to you to say quite simply"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 892166.0,
      "end_time": 897678.0,
      "text": "that you can define how strong a democracy is"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 897678.0,
      "end_time": 902911.0,
      "text": "by how its government treats its child."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 902911.0,
      "end_time": 904967.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t mean children. I mean the child of the state."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 904967.0,
      "end_time": 909934.0,
      "text": "Thanks very much. It&#39;s been an honor. (Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 909934.0,
      "end_time": 912386.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}